Identifiers

1) Identifiers are nothing but the legal name of the java components. 

2) The java component can be:

-> Variables
-> Classes
-> Methods
-> Interface
-> Constant

3) Java 'reserved' keyword cannot be used as an identifier. e.g. public, class, static, void etc..

4) First character of an Identifier should be alphabetic character (a to z), dollar symbol ($), or connection character (_) 
-> (Any number or special character is not permitted)

5) After first character, other character can be combinations of $,_,(a to z),(0 to 9)

6) Special character are not permitted at any case